  "prompt": "Do women lactate when they are pregnant?",
  "response": "Lactation typically occurs after childbirth, not during pregnancy. However, some women may start producing small amounts of colostrum, which is a precursor to breast milk, during the later stages of pregnancy. This is normal and is the body's way of preparing for breastfeeding once the baby is born. Full lactation usually begins a few days postpartum when the hormone prolactin increases and milk production ramps up.",
